  "texts": [
    "In summary, when dealing with difficult, sparse, and clustered data such as hydrocarbon contamination or soil pollution, we need a flexible model that can handle uncertainty and, crucially, remains interpretable.",
    "Because data is limited, it becomes essential to identify and incorporate relevant covariates.",
    "Therefore, the model must be able to handle covariates effectively and transparently.",
    "Bayesian GP-SVC models meet all these criteria, although they come with a high computational cost when N and/or p is large.",
    "Moreover, when working with censored data, the modeling task becomes even more challenging."
  ],
